issues.title: 5.0L V8 Engine Oil Pan Gasket Leak
issues.description: The oil pan gasket on the 5.0L HO engine commonly fails due to age and heat cycles, causing oil leaks that can lead to engine damage if left unchecked.
issues.fix_description: Replace oil pan gasket, clean mating surfaces, and refill with fresh oil
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes and monitoring oil levels

issues.title: T5 Manual Transmission Synchronizer Wear
issues.description: The T5 manual transmission synchros, particularly 2nd and 3rd gear, wear prematurely causing grinding and difficulty shifting.
issues.fix_description: Rebuild transmission with new synchros, or replace transmission
issues.prevention: Proper shifting technique, regular transmission fluid changes, avoid power shifting

issues.title: Mass Air Flow Sensor Failure
issues.description: The MAF sensor commonly fails or becomes contaminated, causing poor engine performance and stalling issues.
issues.fix_description: Clean or replace mass air flow sensor and check air filter
issues.prevention: Regular air filter replacement and avoid aftermarket air intake modifications

issues.title: Rear Differential Gear Whine
issues.description: The 8.8-inch rear differential develops gear whine, particularly in the ring and pinion, due to wear or improper setup.
issues.fix_description: Rebuild differential with new ring and pinion, check backlash and preload
issues.prevention: Regular differential fluid changes, avoid aggressive launches

issues.title: A/C Evaporator Core Leak
issues.description: The A/C evaporator core commonly develops leaks due to corrosion, requiring dashboard removal for replacement.
issues.fix_description: Remove dashboard and replace evaporator core, evacuate and recharge A/C system
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system maintenance and annual refrigerant level checks

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: In-tank electric fuel pump fails, often without warning, leaving the vehicle unable to start or causing sudden stalling.
issues.fix_description: Drop fuel tank and replace fuel pump assembly
issues.prevention: Avoid running fuel tank below 1/4 full, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: TFI Ignition Module Failure
issues.description: The Thick Film Ignition (TFI) module fails when hot, causing no-start conditions until the vehicle cools down.
symptoms: No start when engine is hot
issues.fix_description: Replace TFI module, relocate to fender well for better cooling
issues.prevention: Monitor module temperature, consider relocation kit

issues.title: Door Lock Actuator Failure
issues.description: Power door lock actuators commonly fail, particularly the driver's side, causing doors to not lock or unlock with remote or switch.
issues.fix_description: Replace door lock actuator motor, may require door panel removal
issues.prevention: Regular operation of locks, lubricate lock mechanisms

issues.title: Speedometer Cable Failure
issues.description: The mechanical speedometer cable breaks or binds, causing speedometer needle to bounce or stop working entirely.
issues.fix_description: Replace speedometer cable from transmission to instrument cluster
issues.prevention: Avoid forcing stuck speedometer needle, regular lubrication

issues.title: Upper and Lower Ball Joint Wear
issues.description: Front suspension ball joints wear prematurely, creating safety hazards and poor handling characteristics.
issues.fix_description: Replace upper and lower ball joints, perform wheel alignment
issues.prevention: Regular suspension inspections, avoid potholes and hard impacts

issues.title: Convertible Top Hydraulic Cylinder Leak
issues.description: Convertible models experience hydraulic cylinder leaks that prevent proper top operation and can damage interior components.
issues.fix_description: Rebuild or replace hydraulic cylinders and seals
issues.prevention: Regular top operation to keep seals lubricated, avoid forcing stuck top

issues.title: EGR Valve Carbon Buildup
issues.description: The EGR valve becomes clogged with carbon deposits, causing rough idle, stalling, and failed emissions testing.
issues.fix_description: Clean or replace EGR valve and clean EGR passages
issues.prevention: Regular engine maintenance, use quality fuel, periodic EGR cleaning

editorial.hero_blurb: The Fox Body Mustang GT represents the purest expression of American muscle car DNA from the era when horsepower was king and political correctness didn't exist. This is the Mustang that taught a generation what affordable performance truly meant.
editorial.essence: The Fox Body GT is raw, unfiltered American muscle that prioritizes straight-line thrills over refinement. It's the last of the old-school V8 pony cars that could be built in your garage and modified with basic tools.
editorial.heritage: Born from Ford's need to revitalize the Mustang nameplate, the Fox platform served from 1979-1993 with the 5.0L High Output V8 arriving in 1982. These final years represent the peak evolution of the Fox chassis before the modern SN-95 took over.
editorial.design_philosophy: Engineers focused on maximizing power-to-weight ratio while keeping costs low, creating an honest sports car that prioritized performance over luxury amenities.
editorial.motorsport_history: Dominated SCCA road racing and drag strips throughout the 1980s and early 1990s, becoming the blueprint for grassroots motorsport success with extensive aftermarket support.
editorial.engine_character: The 5.0L Windsor V8 delivers torquey, old-school power with a lumpy idle and aggressive throttle response that builds to a satisfying crescendo at redline.
editorial.transmission_feel: The Borg-Warner T5 manual shifts with mechanical precision but requires deliberate inputs, rewarding smooth technique with satisfying gear changes.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The live rear axle provides classic muscle car drama with occasional wheelhop and snap oversteer, while the front struts offer predictable if not sophisticated handling.
editorial.steering_feel: Manual rack and pinion delivers honest feedback with moderate effort, communicating road surface changes directly to your hands without modern isolation.
editorial.brake_confidence: Four-wheel disc brakes provide adequate stopping power for spirited driving, though extended track use reveals their limitations compared to modern systems.
editorial.sound_signature: The 5.0L produces a distinctive rumbling idle that builds to an aggressive bark under acceleration, especially with aftermarket exhaust modifications.
editorial.ideal_owner: Enthusiasts who appreciate analog driving experiences, weekend wrenchers, and anyone seeking authentic 1990s muscle car character with strong modification potential.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily commuters seeking refinement, drivers wanting modern safety features, or those uncomfortable with basic interior appointments and occasional mechanical quirks.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for rust-free examples with documented maintenance history, as these cars are reaching classic status. The combination of affordable entry price and massive aftermarket support makes them excellent project platforms.

fitment.clearance_notes: May require minor fender adjustment at full lock

expertReviews.title: 1991 Ford Mustang 5.0 "Fox Body" Review - Why It's The ...
pros: Return to form after heavy second generation
cons: Unsophisticated rear axle that skips over bumps
expertReviews.verdict: The Fox Body Mustang delivers on the 80s sport compact experience with good straight-line performance and nostalgic appeal, but handling limitations from the rear suspension geometry and poor steering feedback prevent it from being a complete driver's car. It's best appreciated as a time capsule that prioritizes character over refinement.

expertReviews.title: 1992 Ford Mustang GT [Foxbody] - 9 THINGS YOU SHOUD ...
pros: Excellent pedal box and clutch engagement
cons: Solid rear axle affects handling precision
Steering has play and deadness on center
Interior rattles and coins making noise
Not as sophisticated as modern cars
expertReviews.verdict: This modified 1992 Fox Body Mustang GT delivers an intoxicating driving experience with its supercharged Boss 302 making 450whp and incredible sound. While it lacks the precision of modern cars with its solid rear axle and loose steering, the authentic character, excellent manual transmission, and pure driving joy make it a compelling classic that's simply fun to drive.

expertReviews.title: What makes the Gen 3 Foxbody Mustang GT So Special ...
pros: Popular race platform - easy to work on
Analog driving experience - feels connected to the car
Surprisingly quick feel despite modest power
Spacious interior with usable back seat
Good cargo space with hatchback design
cons: Very analog interior with minimal technology
expertReviews.verdict: The 1993 Fox Body Mustang GT is an iconic piece of American automotive history that still puts a smile on your face 30 years later. While the performance numbers are modest by today's standards (205 hp, 7.1 sec 0-60), the car's light weight and analog driving experience make it feel surprisingly quick and engaging. Ford's most successful body style run ever, selling 2.6 million units, it remains popular with enthusiasts and racers for its simplicity and tuning potential.

While it needs some minor fixes like trim painting, door molding reattachment, and weather stripping replacement, the overall quality and rare color combination make it a worthwhile purchase even if major components needed work.

expertReviews.title: 1991 Mustang GT (Foxbody) // Review!
pros: Saved the Mustang brand from front-wheel drive
Good acceleration feel even with automatic transmission
Actual rear seat room unlike current Mustangs
Historical significance as longest-lived Ford platform
cons: Low original horsepower compared to modern standards
Stock performance modest by today's standards
expertReviews.verdict: The Fox Body Mustang is a true automotive icon that literally saved the Mustang brand. This 1991 GT with its 5.0 V8 represents the perfect bridge between old-school and new-school performance cars. While not fast by today's standards, its lightweight construction, classic styling, and modification potential make it a fantastic enthusiast car. The reviewer was thoroughly impressed with his first Fox Body experience, especially noting how this particular car belongs to a 16-year-old as his first car. Plans for a supercharger upgrade show the platform's potential.
